      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 308,
      "message": "As I understand it, the whole rationale for using StringBuilder is to buy efficiency and limit the need for garbage collection.  It seems to me that if you've gone to that trouble, you shouldn't risk that the java machine may not handle the + operator efficiently.  (The discussion at URL https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1532461/stringbuilder-vs-string-concatenation-in-tostring-in-java may have some bearing.)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3477,
