      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 222,
      "message": "The original logic loops over the mappings and for different keys ensures that there is no mapped value overlap.  The replacement logic loops over the keys and ensures that for each key there is no mapped value overlap.  I find the replacement version slightly easier to read, perhaps because there are fewer angle brackets involved, but I have no reason to believe that they will arrive at different results.  Do you?  Is there reason to believe that one approach is more efficient than the other?  If so, which is which?",
