      "message": "Does the @JsonProperty annotation for the underlying data fields necessitate the introduction of the \"get\" functions?  Both \"set\" functions appear in appc-inbound/appc-design-services/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/appc/design/dbervices/DesignDBService.java and method setUsers also appears in appc-inbound/appc-design-services/provider/src/test/java/org/onap/appc/design/validator/TestDesigndata.java .  Oddly (to me), while the latter file exercises various methods, even when it invokes a \"set\" method and then the associated \"get\" method, it doesn't validate that the latter returns the expected value.  Ought this to be addressed?",
